The paper discusses a linear transmit strategy for multiuser MIMO systems, which falls under the information theory (cs.IT) and networking and internet architecture (cs.NI) sub-categories. The proposed low-complexity precoding algorithms involve QR decompositions and lattice reductions, which are commonly used in signal processing (cs.SI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also mentions achieving maximum diversity order, which is a concept in wireless communication (cs.MM).
